            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="418" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                <head>Municipal Council of Kidderminster</head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Kidderminster</placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-03">May 3, 1865</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>At a meeting of the town council of the borough of Kidderminster, in the
                        county of Worcester, held Wednesday, the 3d day of May, 1865.</p>
                <p>Moved by Mr. Councillor P. Talbot; seconded by Mr. Councillor Boycott—</p>
                <p>That this council, representing the inhabitants of the borough of
                        Kidderminster, desires to give utterance to the feelings of grief and horror
                        at the assassination of President Lincoln, and the attempted murder of Mr.
                        Seward, and to convey to the United States government and people, and to
                        Mrs. Lincoln, an expression of its profound sympathy and sincere condolence.
                        Carried unanimously.</p>
            </div>
